JWT - JSON Web Token

Use - user authorization in web apps

Seesion Token vs JWT Token
Session Token
1. Statefull
2. Store information in server side
3. Suitable for monolithic application

JWT Token
1. Stateless
2. Store information in Client side
3. Suitable for multi instance and Microservice 

JWT Structure
1. Header
2. Payload
3. Signature

jwt.io - we can get info from token 

User Table DDL:
create table user (
       id bigint not null,
        created_at datetime,
        email_id varchar(255),
        gender varchar(255),
        is_active bit,
        login_at datetime,
        login_count integer,
        name varchar(255),
        password varchar(255),
        phone_number varchar(255),
        sso_type varchar(255),
        updated_at datetime,
        user_type varchar(255),
        primary key (id)
    )

